model_explanation: the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ROB," which means Sam gave bananas to Rob and not to anyone else. S2, which states that Sam didn’t give Tom bananas, is consistent with this. Thus, S2 is entailed by S1.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "TOM," which means Sam gave grapes to Tom and not to anyone else. This doesn't entail anything about what fruit Tom did or didn’t get besides grapes. S2, which states that Tom didn’t get oranges, is independent since S1 doesn’t say anything about oranges.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ORANGES," meaning Sam gave Sue oranges and nothing else. If Sam also gave Sue apples, that contradicts S1. So S2 is contradicted by S1.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "SUE," meaning Sam gave bananas only to Sue and not to anyone else. S2 states that Sam didn’t give Rob bananas, and this follows from S1, so S2 is entailed by S1.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ORANGES," meaning Sam gave Tom only oranges and nothing else. Therefore, if Sam gave Tom no other fruit, S2 (that Sam didn’t give Tom bananas) is entailed by S1.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "APPLES," meaning Sam gave Sue only apples and nothing else. That means Sue didn’t get oranges, so S2 is entailed by S1.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "GRAPES," meaning Sam gave Sue only grapes and nothing else. Therefore, S2 (that Sam didn’t give Sue apples) follows from S1, and is entailed.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "ORANGES," meaning Sam gave Ellen only oranges and nothing else. If S2 says Sam also gave Ellen bananas, that contradicts S1. So S2 is contradicted by S1.
the prosodic focus in S1 is on "GRAPES," meaning Sam gave Mary only grapes and nothing else. Therefore, S2, which says Mary didn’t get apples, is entailed by S1.

the prosodic focus in S1 is on "BILL," meaning Sam gave oranges only to Bill and not anyone else. S2 says Mary got oranges. It doesn’t follow from or contradict S1 (which only addressed Bill), so S2 is independent of S1.
